{"source_key":"sha256-c8597aca71664a84bdd657ea13dadbd3","record_index":973,"record_hash":"sha256:9ea5e2ecc116bc131ab9f36d0f521dfd1001d63883960a3b392490dd903e6a13","timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:16:10.427Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"The proposal is directionally right, but it underspecifies the hard part: capture is currently a cheap transcript append, and this turns it into a transaction that depends on workspace graph, diff, commit-tree walking, indexes, and retry semantics. That’s a big lifecycle jump.\\n\\n**Main Risks**\\n\\n1. **Atomicity is still leaky unless every write moves into `apply_edits`.**  \\n   Current code writes session index/schema/source metadata with separate calls, then appends transcript/hash edits atomically afterward: [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:101). The spec says “one logical GitMeta update,” but it should explicitly require *all* session/source/update/turn/index writes in the same batch. Otherwise retries can still leave half-shaped sessions.\\n\\n2. **The pinned GitMeta dependency likely does not have `MetaEdit::SetValue` yet.**  \\n   `but-agentlog` pins `git-meta-lib` directly at [Cargo.toml](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/Cargo.toml:15), and the checked-out API I found only has `ListAppend` and `SetAdd`. Spec tweak: name the minimum git-meta commit/version and add a compile-time checklist item: “turn implementation must not use `handle.set`, `set_add`, or `set_record` for capture writes.”\\n\\n3. **Idempotency by `ordered_new_record_hashes` is fragile under partial previous writes and concurrency.**  \\n   Current dedupe reads `record-hashes`, mutates an in-memory set, then writes later: [gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:55). Two hook processes can both see the same old set and both append the same transcript entries if GitMeta doesn’t serialize at the semantic level. Spec tweak: define concurrent capture behavior explicitly. Either require a repo/GitMeta capture lock, or require post-transaction conflict detection/retry around the dedupe read.\\n\\n4. **Skipping turn creation when zero new records makes retry recovery impossible in one important case.**  \\n   The spe\n[TRUNCATED]\neep generic source data and hash/index fields. Spec tweak: define `provider_turn_key` production per provider and whether it is hashed from raw provider id, source path + id, or event boundary.\\n\\n14. **Future scoring needs more negative evidence fields.**  \\n   The scoring section is good, but the storage model lacks enough “how incomplete was this?” metadata. Spec tweak: add reasoned statuses per sub-observation: `worktree.status`, `stacks.status`, `commit_files.status`, each with `complete|partial|failed|skipped`, plus counts/truncation. One top-level `partial` is too blunt.\\n\\n15. **Sync/retry lifecycle is underdescribed.**  \\n   Hook capture spawns async sync and discards output: [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:123). Local capture can succeed while remote GitMeta sync fails for a long time. Spec tweak: separate local capture durability from remote sync state. Add `last_local_capture_at`; don’t imply review sharing can see turns until sync succeeds.\\n\\n**Spec Tweaks I’d Make**\\n\\n- Add `capture_kind`, `capture_sequence`, and `previous_turn_key` semantics.\\n- Require a capture-level lock or explicit optimistic retry loop around dedupe + previous-turn lookup + write.\\n- Move all capture writes into one `apply_edits` call; no stray `handle.set*`.\\n- Define a path-only environment snapshot API and ban UI diff/hunk assignment from hook capture.\\n- Add caps for commits and branches, not just file paths.\\n- Make backfill environment evidence weak by schema, not just scoring convention.\\n- Canonicalize branch/review/change index keys in the spec.\\n- Add per-section snapshot statuses and truncation fields.\\n- Define index value encoding concretely.\\n- Add a v1 plain-Git fallback shape instead of discovering that hole mid-implementation.\\n\\nBlunt take: the model is good, but the spec currently reads like storage is the hard part. It isn’t. The hard part is making stop-hook capture cheap, idempotent, retryable, and not quietly wrong when the workspace graph is weird.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T02:16:10.427Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}